    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Overcoats with hoods made of duffle (woollen cloth with a thick nap) and with toggle fastenings. Made famous by the British General Montgomery in World War II, so also known as 'monty coats'.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
